    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-07T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-07T10:00:00-05:00" n="186"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/7–747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Keith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-07T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 7, 1947—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1064. When Ambassador Griffis<note n="1" xml:id="d186fn1">Stanton Griffis was
                        actually the appointed ambassador, since he did not present his credentials
                        to President Boleslaw Bierut until July 9. See telegram 1089, from Warsaw,
                            <ref target="#pg_320">p. 320</ref>.</note> called on Foreign Minister
                    today latter took occasion to say that although final decision had not been made
                    he certain Polish Government would accept British-French invitation and be
                    present at meeting in Paris. This decision is different from that which was
                    anticipated by British for British Ambassador told Ambassador Griffis evening
                    sixth that neither he nor Bevin expected Poles would participate.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 1064.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Keith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
